1
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:33,760
BUA LOI

2
00:00:33,840 --> 00:00:36,000
BUA LOI
MENU

3
00:00:37,760 --> 00:00:40,480
Sis, two bowls of bua loi, please.

4
00:00:40,560 --> 00:00:41,720
Sure.

5
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:49,280
One hundred baht.

6
00:00:50,760 --> 00:00:51,600
Huh?

7
00:00:53,680 --> 00:00:57,360
One hundred?
Yesterday, two bowls were only fifty.

8
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:59,560
It's a tough economy, prices have gone up.

9
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:01,000
Do you still want it?

10
00:01:02,440 --> 00:01:03,640
Yes.

11
00:01:04,239 --> 00:01:06,160
- One hundred, right?
- That's right.

12
00:01:07,360 --> 00:01:09,040
Thank you.

13
00:01:11,480 --> 00:01:12,960
Money, money, money…

14
00:01:13,640 --> 00:01:15,120
Everything's about money.

15
00:01:18,960 --> 00:01:21,400
I wanna be rich!

16
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:44,040
You…

17
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,960
Police! Help!

18
00:02:54,040 --> 00:02:55,720
Over here! This way!

19
00:02:56,880 --> 00:03:00,000
Help! Police!
Over here! Someone's shooting!

20
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:02,200
Help! This way!

21
00:03:24,520 --> 00:03:25,400
Hey!

22
00:05:58,800 --> 00:06:01,520
FOUR HOURS EARLIER

23
00:06:05,840 --> 00:06:07,160
You can put it here.

24
00:06:26,880 --> 00:06:28,120
So handsome…

25
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:36,240
Is he crying?

26
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,200
What do we do?

27
00:06:58,120 --> 00:06:59,160
Trai, stop!

28
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:02,960
How did you even get back?
Aren't you still working as an intern?

29
00:07:05,880 --> 00:07:06,880
Where's Dad?

30
00:07:08,160 --> 00:07:09,360
Go get him.

31
00:07:18,080 --> 00:07:19,360
Where is Dad?

32
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:22,520
I'm asking where he is.

33
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:24,960
Dad.

34
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:27,640
Hey, Dad!

35
00:07:28,440 --> 00:07:29,520
Hey!

36
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,040
So you made it here.

37
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:41,480
You steal your own son's girlfriend.
You don't deserve to be anyone's father.

38
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:47,080
Get everyone out. Now.

39
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:49,200
Staff outside, please.

40
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:50,720
- Please go outside.
- Please.

41
00:07:50,800 --> 00:07:52,360
Hurry up, please. Come.

42
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:55,040
Being a billionaire finance tycoon,

43
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:58,800
you can have any woman you want.
Why does it have to be Darin?!

44
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:04,160
And you're marrying the woman I love?

45
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:06,480
What kind of monster are you?

46
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:11,320
Answer me. What kind of monster are you?!

47
00:08:13,280 --> 00:08:16,000
Hey, Trai, stop. Stop!

48
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:43,159
Dad forced you, right?

49
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:46,480
You don't need to be scared.
I won't let him do anything to you.

50
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:48,400
She's not afraid of me.

51
00:08:48,920 --> 00:08:50,480
She's afraid of being poor.

52
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:54,280
I'm going to marry Mr. Tritot.

53
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:57,520
You heard her, didn't you?
Was it clear enough?

54
00:08:58,200 --> 00:09:00,160
The woman you love most,

55
00:09:00,800 --> 00:09:02,000
in the end…

56
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:06,800
could be bought.

57
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:11,120
I don't believe it.

58
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:16,080
Da.

59
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,400
I don't believe you chose this.

60
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:22,720
You don't have to be afraid. Come with me.

61
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:27,440
I'll give everything up,
and we'll start a new life together.

62
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:32,800
Enough, Trai.

63
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:35,560
I'm not going anywhere.

64
00:09:38,560 --> 00:09:39,960
Stop talking nonsense, Trai.

65
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:44,200
Someone like you? Give up everything?

66
00:09:48,680 --> 00:09:51,800
You think I can't live without your money?

67
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,040
Fine!

68
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:58,400
I'll prove to you
that I can survive without it!

69
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:01,120
Go on, then.

70
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:04,080
Da, I love you.

71
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:06,160
Come with me.

72
00:10:15,200 --> 00:10:16,600
I've made my choice.

73
00:10:16,680 --> 00:10:18,640
Leave me alone, Trai.

74
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:31,400
The guests are starting to arrive.

75
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,000
Trai.

76
00:10:34,520 --> 00:10:37,520
Go wait at your condo. We'll talk later.

77
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:38,800
There's nothing left to discuss.

78
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:41,360
It's over. Trai,

79
00:10:41,960 --> 00:10:43,120
go back to England

80
00:10:43,200 --> 00:10:45,840
and finish your internship.
Mr. Lee is waiting.

81
00:10:47,320 --> 00:10:48,240
Take Trai to the airport.

82
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:49,840
Go.

83
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,640
Shit.

84
00:10:54,400 --> 00:10:55,760
Is he dead?

85
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:07,000
I need a favor.

86
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:13,880
No one's picking up.

87
00:11:15,080 --> 00:11:16,360
Is this even the right number?

88
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:18,760
- Ms. Nok's number, right?
- Yeah.

89
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:19,960
I'll check for you.

90
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:23,400
Wait, I've got her secretary's number.

91
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:27,840
- Where is it?
- Hold on, I'm looking.

92
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:29,920
Here it is.

93
00:11:33,280 --> 00:11:34,400
Call it.

94
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:25,680
Police! Help!

95
00:12:25,760 --> 00:12:28,760
Over here! Help! This way!

96
00:12:28,840 --> 00:12:29,680
Hey.

97
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:34,560
Hey!

98
00:12:36,200 --> 00:12:40,160
You need to go now before he comes back.
Come on, hurry.

99
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:46,920
Hey, hey.

100
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:50,440
Help! Help!

101
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:58,840
I stitched it up. He'll wake up in a bit.

102
00:12:58,920 --> 00:13:00,600
Let him sleep here.

103
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:03,920
- Thank you so much, Dr. Bee.
- Sure.

104
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,360
Here's the key.

105
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:11,680
Watch the clinic for me. Turn off
the water and the lights and lock up.

106
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:14,840
- I'm heading out.
- Thank you.

107
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:38,480
You're crying again?

108
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:58,200
Why would you cry over a woman like that?

109
00:14:03,560 --> 00:14:05,680
You're handsome and rich.

110
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:09,920
You could get as many women as you want.

111
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:15,760
Oh? Hey.

112
00:14:16,720 --> 00:14:18,040
Why are you crying even harder?

113
00:14:19,520 --> 00:14:21,080
Hey.

114
00:14:21,160 --> 00:14:24,280
There, there…

115
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:14,680
<i>Smile.</i>

116
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:16,920
Big smile,

117
00:15:17,520 --> 00:15:20,240
so everyone can see just how happy you are

118
00:15:21,040 --> 00:15:23,160
to toss aside that pathetic love

119
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:25,920
and marry a billionaire like me.

120
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:27,640
What do you mean?

121
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:29,120
What do I mean?

122
00:15:33,560 --> 00:15:35,520
Think carefully.

123
00:15:36,160 --> 00:15:37,880
Three years ago,

124
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:41,160
what did you and Trai do?

125
00:15:54,240 --> 00:15:57,800
All this time, I thought Trai was selfish,

126
00:15:57,880 --> 00:16:00,680
that he abandoned me
to face the case alone.

127
00:16:08,920 --> 00:16:11,640
But it was all because you forced him to.

128
00:16:11,720 --> 00:16:14,080
Trai lost his mind because of you.

129
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:19,280
He didn't even finish school.

130
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:21,680
Then you two went and caused trouble,

131
00:16:22,560 --> 00:16:24,760
so I had to send him to England
to escape the charges.

132
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:28,640
And even then, he still went insane
and tried to come back to you.

133
00:16:32,720 --> 00:16:34,520
As his father, I had to deal with it.

134
00:16:36,640 --> 00:16:38,560
I needed to make him wake the hell up,

135
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:41,120
so he'd see

136
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:44,400
that the woman he's obsessed with

137
00:16:45,720 --> 00:16:48,640
doesn't value love
the way he thinks she does.

138
00:16:50,840 --> 00:16:52,200
So you came into my life,

139
00:16:53,400 --> 00:16:55,080
pretended to care,

140
00:16:56,640 --> 00:16:58,480
and married me

141
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:03,040
just because you didn't know
how to get me out of Trai's life?

142
00:17:09,760 --> 00:17:11,359
Let me ask you honestly, Darin.

143
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:13,480
Do you really think

144
00:17:14,240 --> 00:17:15,800
someone like me would like you?

145
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:21,720
If you don't love me, then let me go.

146
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:23,760
I'm not locking you up.

147
00:17:24,400 --> 00:17:26,000
Go, if you want.

148
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:36,680
But I've spent a lot already.

149
00:17:40,320 --> 00:17:42,080
At least make it worth my money.

150
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:52,280
No…

151
00:17:53,880 --> 00:17:55,680
Trai and I, we used to…

152
00:17:57,800 --> 00:17:58,880
So what?

153
00:17:59,840 --> 00:18:00,840
Everyone knows.

154
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:03,640
You chose to marry me.

155
00:18:04,600 --> 00:18:06,960
I didn't force you, Darin.

156
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:12,720
Just be obedient…

157
00:18:15,920 --> 00:18:17,760
and everything will be alright.

158
00:19:03,480 --> 00:19:05,240
- Hey!
- Oh?

159
00:19:11,120 --> 00:19:12,160
Where am I?

160
00:19:12,240 --> 00:19:14,200
A clinic near my place.

161
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:16,320
I brought you to a doctor.

162
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:18,080
Your wound's already been stitched up.

163
00:19:20,320 --> 00:19:22,040
Who was that guy?
Why would he try to kill me?

164
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:23,760
You're asking me?

165
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:26,200
How would I know?

166
00:19:28,120 --> 00:19:29,800
I just happened to run into you,

167
00:19:29,880 --> 00:19:32,200
and I risked my life to save you.

168
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:33,760
Remember?

169
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:39,080
Yeah. Thanks.

170
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:42,640
But a thank you doesn't pay
the doctor's bill.

171
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:46,680
Cash, PromptPay,
or do you wanna scan to pay?

172
00:19:56,560 --> 00:19:59,960
Your phone's totally wrecked.

173
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:04,760
Do you want to go to the hospital

174
00:20:05,520 --> 00:20:07,120
or to report this to the police?

175
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:09,600
I offer secretarial services too.

176
00:20:09,680 --> 00:20:11,320
My fee's not expensive.

177
00:20:15,560 --> 00:20:17,680
Forget it. I don't want to go anywhere.

178
00:20:21,560 --> 00:20:22,840
Oh? Hey.

179
00:20:23,560 --> 00:20:24,440
Hey!

180
00:20:24,520 --> 00:20:27,760
PORRAK POLYCLINIC

181
00:20:29,840 --> 00:20:34,560
Hey, are you leaving? Huh? Hey!

182
00:20:38,440 --> 00:20:39,520
Where are you going?

183
00:20:39,600 --> 00:20:42,560
Hey! Hey, hey.

184
00:20:43,360 --> 00:20:45,320
Why are your legs so damn long?

185
00:20:48,440 --> 00:20:50,840
Hey, are you seriously leaving?

186
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:53,400
Aren't you afraid you're gonna get killed?

187
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:56,840
It doesn't matter if I leave or stay.
Just leave me here.

188
00:20:56,920 --> 00:20:58,120
Hey, wait.

189
00:20:58,640 --> 00:20:59,920
I can't just leave you.

190
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:03,080
The stitches cost 5,000 baht.
How can I just leave you?

191
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:08,880
‪Here.

192
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:10,800
Take it all.

193
00:21:17,520 --> 00:21:19,160
You're giving me all of this?

194
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:30,240
Nothing smells better than this, you know.

195
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:32,040
Hey.

196
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:34,840
Wait, wait.

197
00:21:38,680 --> 00:21:40,400
Thank you so much.

198
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:43,240
Do you know

199
00:21:43,960 --> 00:21:46,240
how long it's been since I've held

200
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:48,720
a fat stack like this?

201
00:21:50,320 --> 00:21:52,480
- Hey, wait.
- What now?

202
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:56,960
Well… life is valuable.

203
00:21:57,040 --> 00:21:58,960
Especially that
of a handsome guy like you.

204
00:21:59,040 --> 00:22:01,200
Extra valuable.

205
00:22:01,840 --> 00:22:04,600
So, do you think your life has value?

206
00:22:05,520 --> 00:22:07,880
- No.
- Yes, it does.

207
00:22:08,840 --> 00:22:10,880
I literally dodged bullets

208
00:22:10,960 --> 00:22:13,400
and went back alone
to save someone valuable like you.

209
00:22:14,960 --> 00:22:18,720
This 10,000 covers
my time and the medical bill,

210
00:22:19,400 --> 00:22:21,480
but the reward for saving your life

211
00:22:22,280 --> 00:22:23,880
is a separate matter, isn't it?

212
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:30,920
How much do you want?

213
00:22:32,080 --> 00:22:33,640
Ooh…

214
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:38,480
If I say it, you'll think I'm greedy.

215
00:22:39,120 --> 00:22:41,080
At this point? Be totally shameless.

216
00:22:42,480 --> 00:22:44,280
Well…

217
00:22:44,960 --> 00:22:48,120
I told you your life is valuable.

218
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:51,960
You wouldn't price yourself
that low, would you?

219
00:22:52,040 --> 00:22:53,440
My life has no value.

220
00:22:54,360 --> 00:22:57,880
I've never done anything for society.
I only cause trouble for other people.

221
00:22:57,960 --> 00:23:00,200
If you want me to price myself,
I'd say zero.

222
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:02,800
Zero?

223
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:05,840
Zero means
you won't give me a single baht?

224
00:23:06,600 --> 00:23:08,440
Fine, then give me 500,000.

225
00:23:08,520 --> 00:23:09,800
- Too much.
- Four.

226
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:12,680
- Too much.
- Okay, three.

227
00:23:13,520 --> 00:23:15,960
That's my absolute lowest, 300,000.

228
00:23:17,520 --> 00:23:18,640
I don't have it.

229
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:21,400
You're holding everything I have.
I have nothing left.

230
00:23:22,840 --> 00:23:24,400
Hey, wait.

231
00:23:29,760 --> 00:23:30,960
But I think…

232
00:23:33,160 --> 00:23:34,280
you do have something.

233
00:23:42,760 --> 00:23:45,040
Happy one-year anniversary, dear.

234
00:23:45,120 --> 00:23:46,360
Do you like it?

235
00:23:47,120 --> 00:23:48,400
I love it.

236
00:24:07,640 --> 00:24:10,680
Take it. It should sell
for the amount you want.

237
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:19,520
Thank you! Thank you so much
from the bottom of my heart!

238
00:24:21,280 --> 00:24:23,400
Okay, I'm going now.

239
00:24:49,440 --> 00:24:53,680
You steal your own son's girlfriend.
You don't deserve to be anyone's father.

240
00:24:56,280 --> 00:24:57,760
<i>Dad…</i>

241
00:24:58,640 --> 00:25:01,160
<i>Dad, please pick up.</i>

242
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:04,080
Dad…

243
00:25:08,720 --> 00:25:10,760
Mom…

244
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:16,120
Mom…

245
00:25:24,680 --> 00:25:28,200
You've never loved anyone.
But when I finally found love…

246
00:25:30,880 --> 00:25:32,520
why did you have to destroy it, Dad?

247
00:25:56,200 --> 00:25:57,320
Your money…

248
00:26:00,080 --> 00:26:01,640
can't buy everything.

249
00:26:03,440 --> 00:26:05,080
At least not my life.

250
00:26:14,840 --> 00:26:16,360
- Hey.
- Hey!

251
00:26:19,560 --> 00:26:20,560
What now?

252
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:24,480
What are you doing by the river?

253
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:28,880
Stay out of it. You already got my money.
Go wherever you want to go.

254
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:31,760
- Listen.
- No. And don't try to stop me.

255
00:26:33,480 --> 00:26:36,480
I'm not stopping you.
I'm just here to tell you that…

256
00:26:38,720 --> 00:26:40,080
the watch you gave me

257
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:43,480
is fake.

258
00:26:43,560 --> 00:26:44,680
Huh?

259
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:53,120
My friend is
a total big shot in this field.

260
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:55,840
He swears on his life

261
00:26:55,920 --> 00:26:57,760
that it's fake.

262
00:26:57,840 --> 00:27:01,160
Where the hell did you even get it?
You got scammed.

263
00:27:03,160 --> 00:27:05,840
Is anything about this woman real at all?

264
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:23,320
That hurts, doesn't it?

265
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:25,400
So much.

266
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:31,080
That's life. But it's okay.

267
00:27:31,160 --> 00:27:34,640
What? Are you gonna say
"You can do it" or something?

268
00:27:34,720 --> 00:27:35,960
No.

269
00:27:36,040 --> 00:27:39,040
I'm gonna say that even without the watch,

270
00:27:39,920 --> 00:27:42,120
a credit card can still withdraw cash.

271
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:50,920
Gosh. Is there anything
in your head besides money?

272
00:27:52,920 --> 00:27:55,400
Am I that obvious?

273
00:27:58,320 --> 00:28:00,600
Please. I'm begging you.
I want to be alone.

274
00:28:00,680 --> 00:28:02,480
Just let me go, alright?

275
00:28:03,080 --> 00:28:05,160
Let me be alone. Okay?

276
00:28:16,160 --> 00:28:18,840
Karma comes in a lot of forms, you know.

277
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:21,680
Sometimes,

278
00:28:22,440 --> 00:28:25,160
it's friends. Sometimes, it's lovers.

279
00:28:26,920 --> 00:28:28,280
Sometimes, it's your dad.

280
00:28:30,600 --> 00:28:32,160
They bring us into this world

281
00:28:32,240 --> 00:28:35,320
and then stomp on our hearts
over and over again.

282
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:38,560
No love. No care.

283
00:28:38,640 --> 00:28:42,000
No attention.
Then why the hell did they even have us?!

284
00:28:43,280 --> 00:28:44,600
Yeah! Damn it!

285
00:28:46,160 --> 00:28:47,480
He only thinks about himself!

286
00:28:49,880 --> 00:28:51,600
When Mom died, where the hell was he?

287
00:28:52,800 --> 00:28:56,160
Only took a few years for him to remarry
and move a new family into the house.

288
00:28:57,000 --> 00:28:58,560
No consideration for his son at all.

289
00:28:58,640 --> 00:29:01,840
Yeah. And then
he makes his son's girlfriend his wife.

290
00:29:01,920 --> 00:29:03,400
Piece of shit!

291
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:07,600
Sorry, sorry.

292
00:29:08,120 --> 00:29:11,280
Just an exclamation.
I didn't mean to curse anyone.

293
00:29:15,840 --> 00:29:16,960
But honestly,

294
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:19,880
when it hurts,

295
00:29:20,640 --> 00:29:21,840
you have to fight even harder.

296
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:23,280
If you die,

297
00:29:23,360 --> 00:29:25,880
the people who hurt you
will just get away with it, right?

298
00:29:27,120 --> 00:29:29,880
I wouldn't accept that. If it were me,

299
00:29:30,480 --> 00:29:35,400
I'd stay alive. I'd fight.
I'd keep messing with them

300
00:29:35,480 --> 00:29:38,640
until the people who hurt me felt guilty

301
00:29:38,720 --> 00:29:40,400
and hurt more than me

302
00:29:40,480 --> 00:29:43,200
a hundred times,
a thousand times, a million times!

303
00:29:51,680 --> 00:29:53,320
You have problems with your dad too?

304
00:29:57,720 --> 00:29:58,960
Who are you?

305
00:30:00,680 --> 00:30:02,000
Have we met before?

306
00:30:08,240 --> 00:30:10,760
If you can't think straight tonight,
wanna sleep at my place?

307
00:30:10,840 --> 00:30:12,040
Huh?

308
00:30:12,880 --> 00:30:14,440
Rent's cheap.

309
00:30:15,080 --> 00:30:18,160
And a free breakfast
will be brought right to your bed.

310
00:30:52,840 --> 00:30:54,000
Pakbung.

311
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:56,520
Why are you home so late?

312
00:30:58,400 --> 00:31:01,160
This is my brother. His name's Kanah.

313
00:31:05,720 --> 00:31:06,560
I forgot to tell you.

314
00:31:07,360 --> 00:31:09,440
My name's Pakbung.

315
00:31:10,360 --> 00:31:11,600
I'm Trai.

316
00:31:18,880 --> 00:31:19,720
Who is he?

317
00:31:22,440 --> 00:31:23,720
He's here to rent a room.

318
00:31:24,520 --> 00:31:25,360
Huh?

319
00:31:28,480 --> 00:31:30,440
Since when do we rent rooms out?

320
00:31:31,520 --> 00:31:32,600
Since just now.

321
00:31:34,520 --> 00:31:35,720
What is this?

322
00:31:46,360 --> 00:31:48,120
Kanah likes sleeping in the living room,

323
00:31:48,640 --> 00:31:51,040
so I'm giving you his room.

324
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:55,200
That's final.

325
00:31:58,800 --> 00:32:02,120
You've had a long night.
Let your heart rest a little, okay?

326
00:32:02,840 --> 00:32:04,920
Go sleep. We'll talk tomorrow.

327
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:26,400
Knock, knock.

328
00:32:42,840 --> 00:32:45,680
- What?
- Why are you so jumpy?

329
00:32:45,760 --> 00:32:48,240
I heard you wake up a long time ago.

330
00:32:48,320 --> 00:32:49,480
You still didn't get out of bed,

331
00:32:49,560 --> 00:32:51,560
so I came to see
what's taking you so long.

332
00:32:52,360 --> 00:32:53,360
I want to be alone.

333
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:00,400
What a mess…

334
00:33:00,480 --> 00:33:02,800
- You look worse than last night.
- I heard that.

335
00:33:05,760 --> 00:33:08,800
If you want to shower, Kanah's clothes

336
00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:11,000
are in the closet.
You can wear whatever you want.

337
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:14,960
And here, your toothbrush.

338
00:33:15,040 --> 00:33:17,680
Do you want black or blue?

339
00:33:19,920 --> 00:33:20,840
Here.

340
00:33:26,800 --> 00:33:27,800
What's the difference?

341
00:33:27,880 --> 00:33:31,000
Black is 35, blue is 50.

342
00:33:32,640 --> 00:33:33,640
It's the best-selling color.

343
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:37,720
Here.

344
00:33:38,800 --> 00:33:40,920
Take the blue one.

345
00:33:46,320 --> 00:33:48,480
Breakfast service is available too.

346
00:33:48,560 --> 00:33:50,120
Soy milk with fried dough is 40.

347
00:33:50,200 --> 00:33:53,520
Pork congee is 55. Seafood is 60.

348
00:33:53,600 --> 00:33:54,760
What would you like?

349
00:33:57,680 --> 00:33:58,800
I'm not going to eat.

350
00:34:00,720 --> 00:34:02,120
Pork congee with egg, then.

351
00:34:08,320 --> 00:34:10,159
Do you remember the PINs on these cards?

352
00:34:10,239 --> 00:34:12,199
If you're too lazy, I can go withdraw cash

353
00:34:12,280 --> 00:34:14,560
and buy you a phone
to contact your family. Do you want that?

354
00:34:15,080 --> 00:34:16,960
No. No contacting. No withdrawing money.

355
00:34:17,040 --> 00:34:18,719
No phone. I don't want anything.

356
00:34:19,440 --> 00:34:22,199
If I use any of that,
they'll know where I am.

357
00:34:25,960 --> 00:34:27,760
How about this?
This room is for rent, right?

358
00:34:28,560 --> 00:34:30,760
I'll stay another month.
I'll pay everything,

359
00:34:30,840 --> 00:34:33,560
clothes, food, toothbrush,

360
00:34:33,639 --> 00:34:35,120
- and--
- And 300,000 for saving you.

361
00:34:37,159 --> 00:34:38,280
Three hundred thousand?

362
00:34:39,040 --> 00:34:40,960
Fine. I'll pay.

363
00:34:41,480 --> 00:34:43,719
Write it down.
I'll pay at the end of the month.

364
00:34:47,920 --> 00:34:49,239
Are you running away from home?

365
00:34:49,960 --> 00:34:52,360
You're really going to give up
your rich life?

366
00:34:53,440 --> 00:34:54,440
Seriously?

367
00:34:56,159 --> 00:34:57,040
Wait.

368
00:35:00,040 --> 00:35:01,120
How do you know I'm rich?

369
00:35:08,600 --> 00:35:09,440
Do you know me?

370
00:35:10,640 --> 00:35:11,480
Well…

371
00:35:12,440 --> 00:35:13,880
if you weren't rich,

372
00:35:16,480 --> 00:35:19,160
you wouldn't wear a suit from this brand.

373
00:35:23,680 --> 00:35:24,640
Get out.

374
00:35:34,880 --> 00:35:36,400
- Hey!
- What!

375
00:35:37,080 --> 00:35:38,040
What now?

376
00:35:38,120 --> 00:35:40,080
If life's really that bad,

377
00:35:40,160 --> 00:35:42,440
you can lie in bed for months if you want.

378
00:35:42,520 --> 00:35:44,040
That's your way.

379
00:35:45,280 --> 00:35:46,800
But do you want to try my way?

380
00:35:48,520 --> 00:35:49,360
How?

381
00:35:57,240 --> 00:35:58,520
This is your way?

382
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:03,520
Between crying my eyes out

383
00:36:03,600 --> 00:36:07,000
and sweating to earn money,
I choose the second one.

384
00:36:07,760 --> 00:36:10,800
When I'm sad, I work.

385
00:36:11,320 --> 00:36:13,600
Work, work, work hard.

386
00:36:14,280 --> 00:36:16,640
When night comes, I pass out.

387
00:36:17,320 --> 00:36:21,480
No time to think. Then, I wake up
in the morning and work again.

388
00:36:21,560 --> 00:36:23,480
And that means making me carry things?

389
00:36:24,360 --> 00:36:25,880
Don't you have a cart or something?

390
00:36:25,960 --> 00:36:27,120
A poor girl like me

391
00:36:27,920 --> 00:36:29,560
doesn't have time to lie around and think.

392
00:36:29,640 --> 00:36:32,680
I work like a hamster on a wheel
just to get through each day.

393
00:36:33,600 --> 00:36:34,880
You'll figure it out eventually.

394
00:36:39,640 --> 00:36:40,680
Follow me.

395
00:36:42,240 --> 00:36:43,240
Hurry up.

396
00:36:43,760 --> 00:36:46,400
What the hell? There were so many of you.

397
00:36:46,480 --> 00:36:48,080
How did you let Trai get away?

398
00:36:48,160 --> 00:36:50,080
I'm sorry, sir.

399
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:55,400
I checked all the CCTV around the condo.
No sign of Mr. Trai at all.

400
00:36:55,480 --> 00:36:57,560
Have you checked every hospital?

401
00:36:58,320 --> 00:36:59,880
Patients, accident cases?

402
00:36:59,960 --> 00:37:02,480
All checked, sir.
No record of Mr. Trai at all.

403
00:37:02,560 --> 00:37:05,800
Track his phone.
Track his financial trail.

404
00:37:05,880 --> 00:37:08,400
Check every account, every credit card.

405
00:37:09,280 --> 00:37:10,680
He must have left some kind of trace.

406
00:37:10,760 --> 00:37:11,640
Yes, sir.

407
00:37:13,960 --> 00:37:15,880
Competition is brutal lately.

408
00:37:16,480 --> 00:37:17,680
I've got plenty of enemies,

409
00:37:18,200 --> 00:37:20,400
hundreds, thousands, who'd want me dead.

410
00:37:21,280 --> 00:37:23,120
Trai is a major shareholder.

411
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:25,560
He's in danger.

412
00:37:26,720 --> 00:37:29,600
Yes. We'll find Mr. Trai
as quickly as possible.

413
00:37:30,240 --> 00:37:31,400
And keep this quiet.

414
00:37:32,000 --> 00:37:33,160
- Yes.
- Don't let it leak.

415
00:37:33,240 --> 00:37:34,560
If it does,

416
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:36,880
the stock will crash.

417
00:37:36,960 --> 00:37:38,120
Yes, sir.

418
00:37:38,640 --> 00:37:40,200
Don't worry, Dad.

419
00:37:40,280 --> 00:37:44,480
I don't think Trai could've gone very far.
I'll try checking with his friends.

420
00:38:01,320 --> 00:38:02,680
It's all taken care of, right?

421
00:38:03,200 --> 00:38:05,600
Mr. Trai won't be
coming back anytime soon.

422
00:38:07,280 --> 00:38:08,960
Disappear for good, Trai.

423
00:38:09,640 --> 00:38:11,920
That way, Dad won't have
to worry about you ever again.

424
00:38:18,640 --> 00:38:21,480
Two, three, four, five, six.

425
00:38:23,800 --> 00:38:26,840
This treadmill offers high-end specs
at an entry-level price. Fit, fit!

426
00:38:26,920 --> 00:38:29,080
Come try it for free,

427
00:38:29,160 --> 00:38:32,000
everyone!

428
00:38:32,080 --> 00:38:34,920
Interested in exercise equipment?
We've got some freebies

429
00:38:36,200 --> 00:38:37,800
as well!

430
00:38:37,880 --> 00:38:41,840
Anyone who's interested
can come take a look and try!

431
00:38:41,920 --> 00:38:44,040
Fit, fit!

432
00:38:44,120 --> 00:38:45,200
NUMBER 1 EXERCISE EQUIPMENT

433
00:38:52,760 --> 00:38:56,400
Who's that? Such a hottie.

434
00:38:56,480 --> 00:38:57,800
Annyeonghaseyo.

435
00:38:57,880 --> 00:38:59,080
Annyeong.

436
00:39:00,720 --> 00:39:03,880
Petch said we're giving away
tons of stuff,

437
00:39:03,960 --> 00:39:05,240
so I brought help to carry boxes.

438
00:39:09,560 --> 00:39:11,480
Hey, hey.

439
00:39:11,560 --> 00:39:14,000
Why aren't you inviting customers?

440
00:39:14,680 --> 00:39:16,160
Are you slacking off?

441
00:39:16,960 --> 00:39:17,960
And where's Petch?

442
00:39:18,560 --> 00:39:21,000
Oh, I'm here.

443
00:39:21,840 --> 00:39:23,960
Ma'am. I was on the phone

444
00:39:24,040 --> 00:39:26,200
finding handsome male models for you.

445
00:39:26,280 --> 00:39:29,840
What? You still haven't found any?

446
00:39:29,920 --> 00:39:33,440
What kind of organizing company is this?
I'm deducting your pay.

447
00:39:33,520 --> 00:39:35,960
Oh, no. You can't deduct it.

448
00:39:37,160 --> 00:39:38,880
My company just opened.

449
00:39:39,520 --> 00:39:43,560
If you deduct my pay, how am I supposed
to pay these promo girls?

450
00:39:43,640 --> 00:39:45,560
I'm begging you, ma'am.

451
00:39:45,640 --> 00:39:48,040
Please don't deduct my pay. I beg you.

452
00:39:49,440 --> 00:39:52,360
Why are you begging her?
It's not our fault.

453
00:39:52,440 --> 00:39:54,360
Wow.

454
00:39:54,440 --> 00:39:56,880
You didn't prepare well.
How is it not your fault?

455
00:39:59,120 --> 00:40:00,000
Huh?

456
00:40:02,240 --> 00:40:05,200
In the contract that I wrote for Petch,

457
00:40:05,280 --> 00:40:08,840
you stated that you'd bring your family
to promote the products.

458
00:40:09,520 --> 00:40:11,120
I even wrote it right here.

459
00:40:12,200 --> 00:40:15,160
And you signed
to acknowledge it right here.

460
00:40:15,240 --> 00:40:16,400
That's right.

461
00:40:17,040 --> 00:40:20,000
Uh… well…

462
00:40:20,080 --> 00:40:23,400
Then I'd like that one. He's handsome.

463
00:40:23,480 --> 00:40:26,600
Come on. Run. Hurry, get on and run.

464
00:40:28,800 --> 00:40:30,040
So handsome.

465
00:40:31,760 --> 00:40:33,200
So handsome.

466
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:35,240
- It's heavy.
- It's okay, it's okay.

467
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:38,520
Pakbung.

468
00:40:38,600 --> 00:40:42,440
Where did you find him? So handsome.
Come on, get on there and run.

469
00:40:42,520 --> 00:40:45,560
Get up there. Run.

470
00:40:45,640 --> 00:40:47,280
There. There.

471
00:40:47,360 --> 00:40:48,920
Wait.

472
00:40:49,920 --> 00:40:51,640
Can you slow it down?

473
00:40:51,720 --> 00:40:53,480
No slowing down for this one.

474
00:40:53,560 --> 00:40:56,280
We have to test it for customers to see

475
00:40:56,360 --> 00:40:58,760
that it "offers high-end specs
at an entry-level price".

476
00:40:58,840 --> 00:41:01,640
No matter how big you are
or how fast you run, it won't shake.

477
00:41:01,720 --> 00:41:03,920
- Just run. Run.
- Wait, wait.

478
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:04,960
My legs are still…

479
00:41:05,040 --> 00:41:07,320
- Keep running.
- No.

480
00:41:07,400 --> 00:41:08,280
Stop.

481
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:13,080
Finally.

482
00:41:13,680 --> 00:41:15,240
So you're not doing it or what?

483
00:41:15,880 --> 00:41:19,320
He can't do it because
I only recruited him to carry boxes.

484
00:41:20,160 --> 00:41:21,600
Yeah. Only carrying boxes.

485
00:41:21,680 --> 00:41:24,560
If you want him to run,
you have to pay extra.

486
00:41:25,760 --> 00:41:27,320
Huh? Wait.

487
00:41:27,400 --> 00:41:29,760
500 for carrying boxes.
5,000 for modeling.

488
00:41:30,360 --> 00:41:32,160
That's our company rate.

489
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:37,520
- Then I'll pay 3,000.
- 4,000.

490
00:41:37,600 --> 00:41:39,440
- 3,500.
- Deal.

491
00:41:39,520 --> 00:41:40,760
Keep running.

492
00:41:41,360 --> 00:41:42,880
Wait, Pakbung. Did you even ask me?

493
00:41:42,960 --> 00:41:46,000
- Stop. He still can't run yet.
- Stopping.

494
00:41:46,080 --> 00:41:47,400
What now?

495
00:41:47,480 --> 00:41:49,480
We agreed on using four male models

496
00:41:49,560 --> 00:41:51,320
across four shifts of two hours each.

497
00:41:51,400 --> 00:41:53,080
Per this quotation here,

498
00:41:53,160 --> 00:41:56,240
it’s 3,500 per person. Times four, that’s…

499
00:41:56,320 --> 00:41:57,480
14,000.

500
00:41:57,560 --> 00:41:58,600
Correct.

501
00:41:58,680 --> 00:42:01,000
And you signed to acknowledge it,
so that's how much you have to pay.

502
00:42:02,120 --> 00:42:05,880
If that's the case, you have to find
three more handsome guys like this

503
00:42:05,960 --> 00:42:08,200
to fill the four shifts, right?

504
00:42:08,280 --> 00:42:11,480
That's right.
And you want someone this handsome?

505
00:42:11,560 --> 00:42:14,360
Then let him do it.
He'll run for all four shifts.

506
00:42:14,440 --> 00:42:16,680
Wait, Pakbung. Four shifts?

507
00:42:16,760 --> 00:42:18,400
One shift and I'm already dying.

508
00:42:18,480 --> 00:42:19,400
Oh, no, no.

509
00:42:19,480 --> 00:42:20,840
You can't do this.

510
00:42:20,920 --> 00:42:23,200
One man running alone won't work.
He'll be exhausted,

511
00:42:23,280 --> 00:42:25,600
and he won't look good anymore.
Who's gonna buy my machines?

512
00:42:25,680 --> 00:42:27,320
How about this?

513
00:42:27,400 --> 00:42:30,680
If it's one person, I'll give you 10,000.

514
00:42:30,760 --> 00:42:31,640
No.

515
00:42:33,240 --> 00:42:35,800
- 12,000.
- 11,000.

516
00:42:35,880 --> 00:42:37,560
11,500.

517
00:42:38,160 --> 00:42:39,760
- Well…
- Deal.

518
00:42:39,840 --> 00:42:42,960
11,500, plus 500 for carrying boxes.

519
00:42:43,040 --> 00:42:45,560
That's 12,000 total.
Let's close at this price.

520
00:42:46,200 --> 00:42:47,360
Deal.

521
00:42:52,520 --> 00:42:54,080
Keep running.

522
00:42:55,560 --> 00:42:57,480
- Hey. Pakbung.
- What?

523
00:42:57,560 --> 00:42:58,960
- Pakbung.
- What?

524
00:42:59,040 --> 00:43:01,040
- Stop it.
- Stop? Stopping.

525
00:43:05,880 --> 00:43:06,960
Are you doing it or not?

526
00:43:07,720 --> 00:43:11,040
If you don't, then go use your card
to withdraw cash, pay me back,

527
00:43:11,560 --> 00:43:12,480
and you can walk away.

528
00:43:14,080 --> 00:43:17,280
Do it? Don't do it? Do it? Don't do it?

529
00:43:17,360 --> 00:43:19,160
Do it? Don't do it?

530
00:43:19,240 --> 00:43:20,200
Do it.

531
00:43:21,760 --> 00:43:26,520
Keep running. Run faster. Go.

532
00:43:28,280 --> 00:43:30,480
Pakbung, you greedy girl.

533
00:43:30,560 --> 00:43:33,640
You psycho. Bloodsucker. Just you wait.

534
00:43:44,240 --> 00:43:45,080
Well?

535
00:43:45,760 --> 00:43:48,720
No leads at all, sir. No cash withdrawals,
no phone usage anywhere.

536
00:43:48,800 --> 00:43:49,920
It's like the device got turned off.

537
00:43:53,120 --> 00:43:54,480
He must be really mad at you.

538
00:43:55,080 --> 00:43:57,240
This time, he's running away for real.

539
00:43:58,560 --> 00:44:00,880
His stubbornness will never change.

540
00:44:00,960 --> 00:44:03,760
I think we should go out
and do a full ground search, sir.

541
00:44:14,680 --> 00:44:15,560
Dad,

542
00:44:16,120 --> 00:44:19,960
people are starting to find out
that Darin is Trai's ex.

543
00:44:20,040 --> 00:44:22,120
So what? Why does it matter?

544
00:44:22,200 --> 00:44:23,760
It's my personal business.

545
00:44:24,280 --> 00:44:25,960
Nobody, inside or outside the company,
can interfere.

546
00:44:26,600 --> 00:44:29,600
But Trai's name is on Be Rich
as a shareholder.

547
00:44:29,680 --> 00:44:32,640
If outsiders know
he's clashing with you like this,

548
00:44:32,720 --> 00:44:35,600
the company will lose
stability and credibility.

549
00:44:35,680 --> 00:44:36,880
So what's the solution?

550
00:44:37,480 --> 00:44:38,360
You can just

551
00:44:38,880 --> 00:44:41,560
make me a shareholder
in place of Trai for now.

552
00:44:42,480 --> 00:44:44,000
You're taking your brother's shares?

553
00:44:45,440 --> 00:44:47,040
No, Dad.

554
00:44:47,120 --> 00:44:50,880
Once Trai stops resisting you and things
calm down, just transfer them back to him.

555
00:44:50,960 --> 00:44:51,920
What if you don't transfer them back?

556
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:53,600
Why wouldn't I?

557
00:44:53,680 --> 00:44:55,040
What do you think I am?

558
00:44:55,120 --> 00:44:57,120
I'm your son, and Trai is my brother.

559
00:44:57,200 --> 00:44:58,600
You're not my real son.

560
00:45:11,480 --> 00:45:12,480
Is that

561
00:45:13,480 --> 00:45:15,280
what you've felt all along?

562
00:45:16,000 --> 00:45:18,280
No matter how much I do for you,
for this company,

563
00:45:18,360 --> 00:45:20,200
I'll never be your son.

564
00:45:21,200 --> 00:45:22,800
I didn't mean to…

565
00:45:24,960 --> 00:45:26,520
I didn't mean it like that.

566
00:45:27,240 --> 00:45:29,040
I'm saying that

567
00:45:29,120 --> 00:45:30,320
even if

568
00:45:31,040 --> 00:45:33,160
I raised you like my own,

569
00:45:34,080 --> 00:45:35,440
everyone knows

570
00:45:36,440 --> 00:45:38,000
you're my ex-wife's child.

571
00:45:38,080 --> 00:45:41,960
So transferring Trai's shares to your name

572
00:45:43,280 --> 00:45:45,040
doesn't really solve anything.

573
00:45:46,680 --> 00:45:47,800
My whole life,

574
00:45:47,880 --> 00:45:50,640
I've never even known
who my biological father was.

575
00:45:50,720 --> 00:45:52,880
I only have one father, and that's you.

576
00:45:53,520 --> 00:45:57,400
I do everything, follow every order.

577
00:45:58,400 --> 00:46:01,160
But Trai,
he resists you, rejects everything.

578
00:46:01,240 --> 00:46:05,080
Isn't that proof enough
of how much I love you?

579
00:46:05,160 --> 00:46:06,200
I know. I know.

580
00:46:06,280 --> 00:46:08,440
Don't take what I said today to heart.

581
00:46:09,680 --> 00:46:10,840
I'm not in a good mood.

582
00:46:12,440 --> 00:46:13,320
Sorry.

583
00:46:18,280 --> 00:46:19,480
Get to work.

584
00:46:36,120 --> 00:46:38,520
Here, an electrolyte drink.

585
00:46:44,480 --> 00:46:45,320
Take it, will you?

586
00:46:50,400 --> 00:46:53,200
I know that lady well.

587
00:46:53,280 --> 00:46:55,760
She'll come and yell
for a bit and then leave.

588
00:46:55,840 --> 00:46:57,840
I'm not actually
making you do four shifts.

589
00:46:58,480 --> 00:47:00,360
Well…

590
00:47:00,440 --> 00:47:02,320
Just one day of work

591
00:47:02,840 --> 00:47:04,880
and you're already making
10,000, you know.

592
00:47:11,440 --> 00:47:12,600
Here. a cooling cloth,

593
00:47:13,760 --> 00:47:15,320
so you'll feel refreshed.

594
00:47:18,840 --> 00:47:20,400
Hey, hey.

595
00:47:23,120 --> 00:47:24,280
How can you be so stingy?

596
00:47:28,440 --> 00:47:32,000
Kanah has asthma,
but he's pushing through med school.

597
00:47:35,560 --> 00:47:37,920
Studying that hard
even though he's not healthy?

598
00:47:38,000 --> 00:47:40,160
Yes. Tuition's expensive.

599
00:47:40,240 --> 00:47:43,200
The meds he needs are crazy expensive too.

600
00:47:44,240 --> 00:47:45,960
And there's also…

601
00:47:48,600 --> 00:47:49,440
Forget it.

602
00:47:52,160 --> 00:47:55,320
Why does a pretty girl like you
have to work this hard?

603
00:47:58,520 --> 00:47:59,720
I'm pretty?

604
00:48:04,520 --> 00:48:05,720
Is that a compliment?

605
00:48:16,320 --> 00:48:18,560
Aw, look who's getting flustered.

606
00:48:19,360 --> 00:48:21,880
Wow, I must be really pretty.

607
00:48:21,960 --> 00:48:25,240
Hey, that's not what I meant.

608
00:48:25,320 --> 00:48:26,440
I just meant…

609
00:48:27,440 --> 00:48:30,400
isn't there some other way?
You don't have to work this hard.

610
00:48:31,760 --> 00:48:32,960
Like?

611
00:48:33,480 --> 00:48:35,840
Get a rich boyfriend. Do you have one?

612
00:48:37,080 --> 00:48:38,480
First, you say I'm pretty,

613
00:48:39,640 --> 00:48:41,600
and now you're asking
if I have a boyfriend.

614
00:48:42,920 --> 00:48:44,960
Wow…

615
00:48:45,040 --> 00:48:48,480
- Well, well.
- Wow, wow.

616
00:48:49,760 --> 00:48:52,680
Pakbung, I'm your best friend.

617
00:48:52,760 --> 00:48:54,800
You bring a guy here
and don't even tell me about him?

618
00:48:54,880 --> 00:48:58,400
Yeah! Normally, the three of us
share everything, split three ways.

619
00:48:58,480 --> 00:49:01,720
This guy should be shared too.

620
00:49:02,880 --> 00:49:04,120
Stop.

621
00:49:07,440 --> 00:49:10,600
This is business. He's renting my place.

622
00:49:10,680 --> 00:49:12,080
Renting your place?

623
00:49:12,680 --> 00:49:13,520
Why?

624
00:49:13,600 --> 00:49:17,560
Because if he stays somewhere else
like a hotel, he has to show his ID card.

625
00:49:18,360 --> 00:49:20,120
Scared of getting ID-checked?

626
00:49:20,720 --> 00:49:22,760
Is he running from the law or what?

627
00:49:24,040 --> 00:49:28,000
Anyway, your face looks familiar.
Are you an actor?

628
00:49:31,120 --> 00:49:34,320
I'm just here to travel and get
some experience. I'll be leaving soon.

629
00:49:41,320 --> 00:49:42,440
This drink's free, right?

630
00:49:47,760 --> 00:49:48,880
What is this, Mr. Tritot?

631
00:49:49,520 --> 00:49:51,200
I don't like marriage certificates.

632
00:49:51,880 --> 00:49:53,080
They don't specify anything.

633
00:49:56,320 --> 00:49:57,800
I prefer contracts.

634
00:49:59,040 --> 00:50:02,040
Everything's written clearly.
No fighting later.

635
00:50:02,120 --> 00:50:04,440
But I'm your wife.

636
00:50:04,520 --> 00:50:07,800
So? Didn't you read it?

637
00:50:07,880 --> 00:50:11,200
Clause 5 clearly states you're
not allowed to interfere in my workplace

638
00:50:11,720 --> 00:50:15,440
without my permission.
Go home. I'm working.

639
00:50:15,520 --> 00:50:19,400
If you had told me from the beginning
what I'd have to face,

640
00:50:20,680 --> 00:50:22,960
I would've run away.
I wouldn't have married you.

641
00:50:23,640 --> 00:50:24,640
Go on.

642
00:50:25,160 --> 00:50:28,080
It's not too late.
The contract isn't signed yet.

643
00:50:28,600 --> 00:50:29,640
Leave. Go.

644
00:50:33,000 --> 00:50:34,040
You don't dare to?

645
00:50:37,600 --> 00:50:40,000
You know it well, don't you?

646
00:50:40,960 --> 00:50:42,520
Second-hand goods,

647
00:50:44,880 --> 00:50:46,760
especially those with defects,

648
00:50:49,200 --> 00:50:51,120
are hard to sell.

649
00:50:52,240 --> 00:50:53,320
And I paid

650
00:50:53,400 --> 00:50:56,240
way above market price.

651
00:50:57,600 --> 00:50:58,920
Go ahead.

652
00:50:59,720 --> 00:51:02,680
Try selling yourself like before.
See if you'll get the same price.

653
00:51:03,640 --> 00:51:04,560
I've never sold myself.

654
00:51:06,920 --> 00:51:08,400
Are you sure?

655
00:51:13,960 --> 00:51:16,200
If something can be traded for money,

656
00:51:17,960 --> 00:51:18,800
then it's for sale.

657
00:51:25,000 --> 00:51:26,120
Mr. Tritot.

658
00:51:29,960 --> 00:51:30,920
Enough.

659
00:51:31,000 --> 00:51:32,600
Having no money is bad enough.

660
00:51:33,360 --> 00:51:35,520
But at least have a brain
and some manners, Darin.

661
00:51:38,960 --> 00:51:41,360
Then I should thank you,

662
00:51:42,480 --> 00:51:44,840
for ruining my life completely.

663
00:51:47,880 --> 00:51:48,880
Then thank me.

664
00:52:21,880 --> 00:52:23,240
Wait.

665
00:52:34,680 --> 00:52:36,080
If you're going to stay,

666
00:52:36,840 --> 00:52:38,160
then sign this contract.

667
00:52:38,800 --> 00:52:41,440
Or do you have other ways
to make money than staying with him?

668
00:52:43,640 --> 00:52:46,880
You people are really good
at looking down on others.

669
00:52:48,480 --> 00:52:50,520
Here. Take it.

670
00:52:52,600 --> 00:52:55,400
This won't lower your dignity, Darin.

671
00:53:01,040 --> 00:53:04,720
How could you lower what you don't have,

672
00:53:06,040 --> 00:53:06,920
right?

673
00:53:15,240 --> 00:53:19,040
Mr. Tritot is willing to do anything
to pull Trai away from me.

674
00:53:20,760 --> 00:53:23,080
I'm curious. If it were you,

675
00:53:23,160 --> 00:53:25,160
would your father go this far?

676
00:53:27,480 --> 00:53:29,600
I've only been here a few days,

677
00:53:30,200 --> 00:53:31,720
and I can already guess the answer.

678
00:53:33,320 --> 00:53:34,840
A real son

679
00:53:35,760 --> 00:53:37,320
versus a son from the mistress.

680
00:53:44,320 --> 00:53:45,800
You think I'll fall for that?

681
00:53:45,880 --> 00:53:49,000
Let me tell you something.
If you want to stay here,

682
00:53:49,560 --> 00:53:52,400
then get your head straight
and adjust your mindset.

683
00:53:53,160 --> 00:53:56,280
But if you can't take it, then leave.

684
00:54:34,000 --> 00:54:35,960
Excuse me, have you ever seen this person?

685
00:54:36,040 --> 00:54:37,200
No.

686
00:54:37,840 --> 00:54:39,920
- No.
- I've never seen him.

687
00:54:40,000 --> 00:54:41,080
Have you seen the man in this photo?

688
00:54:42,040 --> 00:54:43,160
Have you seen this man?

689
00:54:45,880 --> 00:54:49,280
His last location pinged around here.
Why has nobody seen him?

690
00:54:49,360 --> 00:54:51,280
But there are a lot of people
living around here.

691
00:54:52,880 --> 00:54:55,840
He couldn't have gone far.
I think he's somewhere around here.

692
00:54:56,960 --> 00:54:58,840
- Here we go.
- Wow, wow.

693
00:54:58,920 --> 00:55:01,520
- Papaya salad.
- Come on.

694
00:55:01,600 --> 00:55:02,560
It looks so good.

695
00:55:02,640 --> 00:55:04,840
- Can we eat right now?
- Let's eat now.

696
00:55:05,520 --> 00:55:08,120
- Move over here.
- Which one should I start with?

697
00:55:09,720 --> 00:55:11,560
Wow, it looks good.

698
00:55:14,280 --> 00:55:15,800
The money already came in.

699
00:55:23,320 --> 00:55:24,280
Come on!

700
00:55:30,120 --> 00:55:33,600
Hey. This is all because of you, Pakbung.

701
00:55:33,680 --> 00:55:35,440
You helped negotiate for me.

702
00:55:35,520 --> 00:55:38,760
Petch, you're starting a company.

703
00:55:38,840 --> 00:55:40,200
You've gotta be a little tough.

704
00:55:40,280 --> 00:55:42,240
How can you let people
take advantage of you?

705
00:55:43,320 --> 00:55:45,320
Well, I…

706
00:55:47,160 --> 00:55:49,400
Come on. I'm ready to get rich.

707
00:55:52,720 --> 00:55:55,040
So fast. Here.

708
00:55:55,120 --> 00:55:58,240
Transfer Niuniu and Samlee's cuts
to me too.

709
00:56:08,760 --> 00:56:10,120
Transfer it to her.

710
00:56:14,520 --> 00:56:16,440
Fine, fine. Whatever.

711
00:56:17,200 --> 00:56:20,560
We don't need to use it right away.
Transfer it to Pakbung.

712
00:56:21,520 --> 00:56:23,440
Hey.

713
00:56:23,520 --> 00:56:24,800
Their money should be their own.

714
00:56:25,560 --> 00:56:27,680
How can you take your friends' pay
and keep it all for yourself?

715
00:56:31,120 --> 00:56:33,160
And for his part, transfer it to me too.

716
00:56:33,680 --> 00:56:34,600
Hey.

717
00:56:38,200 --> 00:56:40,800
Rent, food, living expenses,
taking care of you, everything.

718
00:56:41,960 --> 00:56:45,080
You said you're staying another month.
Consider it as an advance payment.

719
00:56:48,800 --> 00:56:50,400
You're going to take care of me, right?

720
00:56:53,960 --> 00:56:56,640
Every baht will be worth it.

721
00:56:59,000 --> 00:57:01,960
Fine. If you're taking care of me,

722
00:57:03,840 --> 00:57:06,360
then you have to provide service
according to my standards only.

723
00:57:21,200 --> 00:57:22,480
It's…

724
00:57:23,200 --> 00:57:25,280
Didn't you say you were going
to live independently?

725
00:57:25,360 --> 00:57:28,000
- Are you picking a fight?
- Die! Take it!

726
00:57:30,640 --> 00:57:32,000
Hey, stop!

727
00:57:33,480 --> 00:57:34,400
Money!

728
00:57:34,480 --> 00:57:35,280
Hey!

729
00:57:35,360 --> 00:57:38,440
If Trai never liked your business
and loves his freedom,

730
00:57:38,520 --> 00:57:39,720
why not just let him go?

731
00:57:39,800 --> 00:57:42,320
He's my son. He has to come back here.

732
00:57:42,920 --> 00:57:44,880
But I'm not as good
at making money as Pakbung.

733
00:57:44,960 --> 00:57:46,960
How could she think about money
with every breath?

734
00:57:47,040 --> 00:57:49,360
You're only good at making money.
Why don't you try

735
00:57:49,440 --> 00:57:51,320
getting a man?

736
00:57:52,840 --> 00:57:55,120
<i>Your mom didn't die here, right?</i>

737
00:57:55,200 --> 00:57:57,680
<i>Did some kids die here too?</i>

738
00:57:57,760 --> 00:57:58,680
You wanna meet them?

739
00:58:02,040 --> 00:58:04,680
100 for the glass, 500 for the wine glass.

740
00:58:04,760 --> 00:58:06,000
Break it and you pay.

741
00:58:06,080 --> 00:58:07,360
So stingy.

742
00:58:07,440 --> 00:58:08,680
Dad?

743
00:58:58,960 --> 00:59:01,080
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
